    <rich_text>Metasploitable 2 Reconnaissance &amp; Vulnerability Analysis Authors: Andersson David Sánchez Méndez &amp; Cristian Santiago Pedraza Rodríguez Target IP: 192.168.106.129 Attacker: 192.168.106.128 Status: Completed Description: This project contains the structured data, tool outputs, and technical findings derived from the security assessment of a Metasploitable 2 instance.</rich_text>
    <node unique_id="2" master_id="0" name="Methodology" prog_lang="custom-colors" tags="" readonly="0" nosearch_me="0" nosearch_ch="0" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1770504495" ts_lastsave="1770507544">
      <rich_text>Approach: Active Reconnaissance / Black Box. Standard: Technical Security Assessment. 

• Process:
   ◇ Network discovery and connectivity verification (Ping/Ifconfig).
   ◇ Service enumeration and banner grabbing using Nmap.
   ◇ Version analysis and vulnerability mapping (CVE correlation).
   ◇ Evidence integrity verification via SHA256 hashing.

</rich_text>
    </node>
    <node unique_id="3" master_id="0" name="Results" prog_lang="custom-colors" tags="" readonly="0" nosearch_me="0" nosearch_ch="0" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1770504506" ts_lastsave="1770507570">
      <rich_text>Vulnerability Table
</rich_text>
      <rich_text justification="left"></rich_text>
      <rich_text>
Highlighted Finding: Remote Root Compromise (vsftpd 2.3.4) Summary: The FTP service contains a backdoor (CVE-2011-2523) that grants unauthenticated root access. Technical Description: Using a specific character sequence :) in the username triggers a shell listener on port 6200.
</rich_text>
