    <node unique_id="5" master_id="0" name="Recommendations" prog_lang="custom-colors" tags="" readonly="0" nosearch_me="0" nosearch_ch="0" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1770504530" ts_lastsave="1770507865">
      <rich_text>Technical Action Plan:

• Decommission Insecure Services: Disable Telnet (Port 23) and vsftpd 2.3.4 (Port 21).

• Encryption: Transition all administrative traffic to SSH (Port 22).

• Update Cycle: Implement a patch management policy to update Apache and Samba versions, as the current versions are end-of-life (EOL).</rich_text>
    </node>
    <node unique_id="6" master_id="0" name="Notes by tool" prog_lang="custom-colors" tags="" readonly="0" nosearch_me="0" nosearch_ch="0" custom_icon_id="0" is_bold="0" foreground="" ts_creation="1770504586" ts_lastsave="1770507933">
      <rich_text>Nmap (v7.9x):

• Execution: sudo nmap -sS -A -T4 192.168.106.129 -oN nmap_scan.txt. 
• Observation: The -A flag was highly effective for OS detection and script scanning, accurately identifying the vsftpd backdoor and several Samba vulnerabilities without manual scripts.

OpenSSL/Sha256sum:

• Observation: Vital for maintaining the chain of custody. The generated hash matches the one reported in the final Obsidian document.</rich_text>
